WEBVTT

00:04.120 --> 00:06.111
(POLICE CHATTER OVER RADIO)

00:33.560 --> 00:35.198
Ed. No.
Peggy, come here.

00:35.280 --> 00:36.315
This is... You're so
outta line, Sheriff!

00:36.400 --> 00:37.356
Peggy, Peggy!

00:37.440 --> 00:39.033
You can't just ruin people's
lives! Peggy, Peggy.

00:39.120 --> 00:40.190
You come back inside.
No!

00:40.280 --> 00:42.794
Parade them around Main
Street for something they didn't do!

00:42.880 --> 00:44.598
Falsely accused. No.

00:44.680 --> 00:45.795
Peggy.

00:45.880 --> 00:49.669
No! You're not gonna prove
my Ed did anything wrong.

00:49.760 --> 00:50.909
It's unprovable!

00:58.640 --> 01:00.358
(CHATTER OVER RADIO)

01:26.040 --> 01:27.030
(DOOR OPENS)

01:28.480 --> 01:30.039
Heard about the fire.

01:30.120 --> 01:32.031
You okay?
You didn't have to come down.

01:33.440 --> 01:35.317
Mrs. Solverson.
Ed.

01:35.400 --> 01:36.674
I'm worried about you.

01:37.720 --> 01:40.280
Feels like the top might just
spin right off the globe these days

01:40.360 --> 01:41.589
and take you
along with it.

01:42.960 --> 01:44.598
What's that for?
(CHUCKLES)

01:44.680 --> 01:47.752
I'm just imagining you
parachuting into the Mekong Delta,

01:47.840 --> 01:50.434
telling the black pajamas
to leave your husband alone.

01:51.040 --> 01:52.269
Shoulda.

01:52.360 --> 01:54.954
Coulda saved a lotta lives if wives
and mothers from both sides came

01:55.040 --> 01:57.111
and dragged their fool
men home by the ear.

01:58.720 --> 02:00.631
Anything I can do
to help this mess?

02:00.720 --> 02:03.838
Yeah, you can take
Noreen home with you.

02:04.360 --> 02:05.794
Her place burned
down with the shop

02:05.880 --> 02:07.632
and we both know
she's just a kid,

02:07.720 --> 02:09.119
emancipated or not.

02:09.199 --> 02:10.395
Noreen.

02:11.039 --> 02:12.360
Hey, Ed.

02:12.440 --> 02:13.475
I told 'em what you said.

02:13.560 --> 02:14.789
Quiet now. Both of you.

02:16.360 --> 02:17.589
Come home soon.

02:17.680 --> 02:19.512
We both know
that's not likely.

02:22.840 --> 02:24.114
Come on, dear.

02:24.200 --> 02:26.191
Let's get you
home and in a bath.

02:26.280 --> 02:28.430
I'll make us some cocoa.
All right?

02:28.520 --> 02:30.033
She's a nice lady.
Shut up.

02:32.640 --> 02:34.153
GARFIELD: Time
for your phone call.

02:52.120 --> 02:53.155
(PHONE RINGING)

03:04.920 --> 03:06.115
Five minutes.

03:14.200 --> 03:15.190
I was thinking about

03:15.280 --> 03:16.270
Elron the other day.

03:17.600 --> 03:18.795
Before?

03:19.600 --> 03:23.673
His face, you know,
trying to remember...

03:26.080 --> 03:28.754
I was 10 when they came.

03:31.600 --> 03:36.595
Soldiers in uniform
with that folded-up flag.

03:39.640 --> 03:41.472
You were in Chicago,
I think.

03:43.200 --> 03:44.395
Mom says.

03:49.440 --> 03:52.000
There's that picture in the
hall, with you and all the kids,

03:53.200 --> 03:54.918
that winter in Bear Lake.

03:58.560 --> 04:00.233
Everyone else in coats,

04:01.880 --> 04:05.874
but Elron's in a T-shirt,
making muscles.

04:09.840 --> 04:14.437
And what would he
do now, you know?

04:15.400 --> 04:17.789
Now, with this.

04:21.839 --> 04:24.070
'Cause he was the oldest,
right?

04:24.240 --> 04:25.230
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

04:25.800 --> 04:27.029
Not Dodd.

04:35.920 --> 04:37.035
What?
(DOOR CREAKING OPEN)

04:37.120 --> 04:40.078
Uncle. Charlie's
on the phone.

04:54.040 --> 04:55.075
What?

04:59.720 --> 05:00.710
(CHUCKLING)

05:03.840 --> 05:04.955
I get it.

05:05.040 --> 05:07.236
You don't have
respect for anything.

05:07.320 --> 05:11.871
But do you know
what a whore's life is?

05:11.960 --> 05:13.234
Come on now.

05:14.120 --> 05:16.475
I'm serious. This is
me looking out for you.

05:18.160 --> 05:19.833
Some career advice.

05:20.880 --> 05:23.838
A whore's life is
five good years,

05:23.920 --> 05:25.558
five bad years,

05:25.640 --> 05:27.756
and then some
half-dick sweat stain

05:27.840 --> 05:29.877
grinds you out
like a cigarette.

05:30.920 --> 05:34.550
Like a goddamn
spent cigarette.

05:34.640 --> 05:38.076
My son? You sent
my goddamn son?

05:38.200 --> 05:39.190
(GRUNTS)

05:40.600 --> 05:41.590
(GROANS)

05:46.720 --> 05:48.552
Jesus! Will you cut it out!

05:48.680 --> 05:52.275
C'mon, Bear! Will somebody
get him off me? (GUN COCKING)

05:55.360 --> 05:57.033
You better stop now.

05:58.280 --> 05:59.315
Okay.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.471
You've been asking for it for
days now, and now it's time.

06:01.560 --> 06:03.710
Tell your man, "Walk
away," and we'll see.

06:03.840 --> 06:05.433
You're getting
the belt, kid.

06:05.520 --> 06:06.840
Strap or buckle?

06:08.280 --> 06:11.033
You think you're... Belt was
dad's thing, and you're not...

06:11.120 --> 06:13.031
The kid said
he was ready.

06:13.120 --> 06:15.839
Said it should be family that
pulls the trigger, which is true.

06:17.400 --> 06:18.720
He's 17.

06:20.480 --> 06:21.879
He's got a crippled arm.

06:21.960 --> 06:23.519
Now see, I don't see that.

06:23.600 --> 06:26.558
I see heart and will.
I see spirit.

06:26.640 --> 06:29.712
I see Grandpa
after the war. Right, Pop?

06:29.800 --> 06:32.155
Grandpa, who stows away
on a boat,

06:32.240 --> 06:34.311
comes to America
and builds an empire.

06:35.120 --> 06:37.680
Compared to that, what
have you ever done?

06:37.760 --> 06:39.080
Or me?

06:39.160 --> 06:40.480
Arm or no arm?

06:41.800 --> 06:46.158
Now, you can have
the strap or the buckle.

06:46.240 --> 06:48.151
"Cause I can't have you
knocking me around,

06:48.240 --> 06:49.435
not in front of the men.

06:52.640 --> 06:55.359
Give me the buckle,
you piece of shit.

06:55.440 --> 06:56.794
That's my boy.

06:58.680 --> 07:00.478
FLOYD: No!

07:00.560 --> 07:01.994
No!

07:02.080 --> 07:05.436
None of your bullshit!
Not today.

07:05.520 --> 07:08.080
You'll kill us all, you
split this family apart!

07:10.680 --> 07:12.034
Now tell me
what happened.

07:12.760 --> 07:14.273
(ENGINES STARTING)

07:24.160 --> 07:26.197
Bring back my grandson.

07:26.280 --> 07:28.112
No excuses.

07:28.200 --> 07:30.555
I'll call up to Winnipeg,
tell "em he's coming.

07:30.640 --> 07:32.313
He can stay there
till things cool down.

07:34.000 --> 07:36.833
And you, while he's
seeing to the boy,

07:36.920 --> 07:39.070
you take care
of this butcher.

07:39.160 --> 07:40.480
He doesn't live
through the night.

07:40.560 --> 07:42.870
Already dead, believe me.
He just doesn't know it.

07:44.320 --> 07:46.834
(ENGINES STARTING)

07:49.560 --> 07:50.550
(DIALING PHONE)

07:56.360 --> 07:58.112
(PHONE RINGING)

08:20.240 --> 08:21.230
(CLEARS THROAT)

08:21.320 --> 08:24.119
This better be
state-secret-level information.

08:24.200 --> 08:25.270
SIMONE: They all left.

08:25.400 --> 08:26.435
Who all?

08:26.520 --> 08:28.955
Dodd and Bear,
and maybe half a dozen...

08:29.040 --> 08:30.110
Going?

08:30.200 --> 08:31.713
He called me a whore.

08:31.800 --> 08:34.792
Well, darling,
technically...

08:34.880 --> 08:36.234
It's my body.

08:36.320 --> 08:37.640
I got every right to...

08:37.720 --> 08:38.914
Of course you do.

08:39.080 --> 08:41.434
We're in full agreement,
you and me. (SIGHS)

08:43.400 --> 08:45.960
A beautiful body and you
can do what you want with it.

08:47.520 --> 08:50.638
But right now
I need you to tell me,

08:50.720 --> 08:53.360
your dad and the others,
where are they headed?

08:53.440 --> 08:55.909
They're going to
that town in Minnesota.

08:56.000 --> 08:57.957
Where the judge...
Luverne.

08:58.040 --> 09:00.600
Yeah, Luverne.

09:01.560 --> 09:04.598
And I want you to...
You're gonna...

09:07.080 --> 09:09.071
Get the hell outta here.

09:13.480 --> 09:15.312
MIKE: Did I lose
you there, sweetheart?

09:16.800 --> 09:18.757
You're gonna kill him for me.

09:18.840 --> 09:20.513
Your dad?
He's not...

09:21.600 --> 09:23.398
Ozzie was a dad.

09:23.480 --> 09:26.199
On the TV, shit,
Mr. French is more of a...

09:26.280 --> 09:27.600
How long ago
did they leave?

09:27.680 --> 09:32.277
Just... (SIGHS)
Maybe half an hour ago.

09:32.360 --> 09:33.998
Took a whole army, almost.

09:34.080 --> 09:35.309
Okay, baby.

09:37.200 --> 09:41.159
Any last message for
your dad when I see him?

09:45.920 --> 09:46.990
Yeah.

09:48.080 --> 09:51.675
Tell him, "Kiss my grits."

