11:35.640 --> 11:38.280
Well, that explains
the beauty mags.

11:38.360 --> 11:40.636
Well, there's more to life
than Minnesota, you know.

11:42.760 --> 11:44.034
Do you think, uh...

11:44.120 --> 11:45.519
I know there's
a lot of questions,

11:45.640 --> 11:49.076
but I got this
seminar tomorrow.

11:49.160 --> 11:50.480
Lifespring?

11:50.560 --> 11:53.074
And I gotta drive up to
Sioux Falls first thing. So...

11:53.720 --> 11:55.870
Um... (SIGHS)

11:55.960 --> 11:59.271
Well, now, I got five
dead since Saturday,

12:00.280 --> 12:03.238
including the one tonight in
the burned-down butcher shop.

12:03.320 --> 12:06.199
And your husband is
currently in jail,

12:06.280 --> 12:09.557
so, I wouldn't count on
getting there early.

12:09.640 --> 12:13.952
No, I mean, that's terrible,
but what can Ed... I mean...

12:14.040 --> 12:15.439
(SIGHS)

12:16.640 --> 12:18.233
Attempted robbery and
those two men at the shop...

12:18.320 --> 12:20.516
It wasn't a robbery, Peggy.

12:20.600 --> 12:23.672
Those men came for your
husband. They came to kill him.

12:24.680 --> 12:26.751
You don't know that
for sure, Sheriff.

12:26.840 --> 12:28.478
You're just trying to be
dramatic. Trying to scare me.

12:28.600 --> 12:30.193
I assure you, I am not.

12:30.280 --> 12:31.429
And when I say
five dead,

12:31.560 --> 12:34.074
I'm only talking about
inside the city limits.

12:34.160 --> 12:38.757
Reports are 15 more bodies,
15 more bodies, up in Fargo.

12:38.840 --> 12:42.549
This is a turf war between
the Kansas City mob

12:42.640 --> 12:45.439
and this Gerhardt family you've
gotten yourself mixed up with.

12:45.520 --> 12:46.954
Stop saying that!

12:47.040 --> 12:49.793
Me and Ed,
we're just bystanders.

12:49.880 --> 12:52.599
Not even. Disconnected.

12:52.680 --> 12:57.516
Him with the shop, and me, just
trying to actualize fully, you know?

12:58.520 --> 13:00.272
Be the best me I can be,

13:00.360 --> 13:02.112
because these are
modern times, you know?

13:02.200 --> 13:03.873
And a woman, well, she
just doesn't have to be

13:03.960 --> 13:05.280
a wife and a mother
no more.

13:05.360 --> 13:08.079
She can be... There's
nothing she can't be.

13:10.040 --> 13:11.360
You're a little touched,
aren't you?

13:13.840 --> 13:14.875
What?

13:14.960 --> 13:16.189
It's not that there's
anything wrong with that.

13:16.280 --> 13:17.918
Don't get me wrong.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.594
It's just the time and place
in which you're...

13:20.680 --> 13:23.718
Well, you know, if you mean
I got dreams, then, yeah.

13:23.800 --> 13:28.192
And maybe I don't see it all like
everybody else, but I got plans.

13:28.280 --> 13:31.910
<i>We got plans and you can't
just come in here and derail...</i>

13:32.040 --> 13:33.474
Yeah, Peggy.

13:33.560 --> 13:35.631
They tried to
Kill your husband.

13:35.720 --> 13:37.313
I mean, they burned
down his shop.

13:37.400 --> 13:39.232
You think that's
the end of it?

13:42.120 --> 13:45.158
Well, I mean,
look, right?

13:45.240 --> 13:48.949
Ed, he really...
He loved that place.

13:50.240 --> 13:53.278
(CLICKS TONGUE) But
life's a journey, you know?

13:53.360 --> 13:55.078
That's what
John Hanley Sr. says.

13:55.160 --> 13:57.515
He's the founder
of Lifespring.

13:57.600 --> 14:00.718
Life's a journey, and the one
thing you don't do on a journey

14:00.800 --> 14:02.837
is stay in one place, right?

14:03.960 --> 14:07.954
So, maybe we'll, I don't
know, go to California or...

14:08.040 --> 14:09.474
California.
...some place.

14:09.560 --> 14:10.994
Now that the shop's gone...

14:11.120 --> 14:13.191
Peggy,

14:13.280 --> 14:17.319
before you, uh, before you start
making plans, you should know

14:17.400 --> 14:19.550
I got a forensic
team coming down

14:19.640 --> 14:21.711
from the Twin Cities
in the morning.

14:21.800 --> 14:24.110
And I know
it's been repaired,

14:24.200 --> 14:27.192
but we're gonna check
your car for blood.

14:27.280 --> 14:29.351
Microscopically, I mean.

14:29.440 --> 14:32.717
Which you'd be amazed
at what we can find

14:32.800 --> 14:34.393
on the atomic
level these days.

14:34.480 --> 14:38.872
No. I mean, you can't
do that, of course,

14:38.960 --> 14:41.076
without permission
from the owner.

14:41.160 --> 14:44.312
You know? So... Oh, we got
permission about an hour ago.

14:44.400 --> 14:46.869
You sold the car to
Sonny Greer, didn't you?

14:46.960 --> 14:49.190
Earlier? At the body shop?

14:49.280 --> 14:52.238
And Sonny now is
the owner on record.

14:52.320 --> 14:53.913
And he was more
than happy to... No.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.150
No, you can't. That's...

14:56.240 --> 14:58.516
Hold on...
Peggy. Peggy.

14:58.600 --> 15:00.193
I'm serious now.

15:02.040 --> 15:06.034
Better you tell me before
I get a fistful of evidence.

15:06.120 --> 15:10.353
What happened that night when
you hit Rye Gerhardt with your car?

15:13.880 --> 15:15.075
ED: I'm the victim here.

15:15.440 --> 15:16.953
Ed.

15:19.120 --> 15:20.599
I mean, 'cause...

15:20.680 --> 15:24.230
I sat in your living room last
night and gave you the chance,

15:24.360 --> 15:26.510
you and Peggy both,
I gave you the chance to...

15:26.600 --> 15:30.036
I know, but you
gotta understand.

15:30.120 --> 15:32.316
We're just trying to...
No, me.

15:32.400 --> 15:34.516
I'm just trying to
protect my family.

15:34.600 --> 15:36.910
There was a cleaver
in the man's head, son,

15:37.040 --> 15:38.758
which Noreen said was you.

15:41.840 --> 15:43.353
Not to mention
there's a war going on

15:43.440 --> 15:44.874
up in Fargo that
you may have started

15:44.960 --> 15:46.997
when you ran over that
Gerhardt boy in Peggy's car!

15:47.080 --> 15:49.833
You or (STUTTERS)
Peggy, or both!

15:50.720 --> 15:53.519
This is all just so crazy.

15:53.680 --> 15:54.670
(SCOFFS)

15:55.960 --> 16:00.113
And I can't stop thinking
about that book, Noreen's book.

16:00.200 --> 16:02.271
It's, like, stuck in
my head. What?

16:02.360 --> 16:03.680
What book?

16:03.760 --> 16:06.593
It's about this
guy who, every day,

16:06.680 --> 16:10.196
he pushes this
rock up this hill.

16:10.320 --> 16:11.879
Like a boulder.

16:12.600 --> 16:15.672
And then every night,
it just rolls back down.

16:17.240 --> 16:21.552
But he doesn't stop, you know?
He just... He keeps going.

16:22.800 --> 16:27.078
And he wakes up every day
and he starts pushing.

16:28.640 --> 16:31.473
By which, (STUTTERS)
I guess I'm saying,

16:31.560 --> 16:33.153
it doesn't matter
what they throw at me,

16:33.240 --> 16:35.629
I'm gonna take care
of what's mine. And...

16:39.880 --> 16:42.713
These boys aren't gonna rest
until you're dead, son.

16:43.920 --> 16:45.593
Possibly Peggy, too.

16:47.760 --> 16:49.239
I want a lawyer.

16:49.840 --> 16:50.830
(SIGHS)

16:50.920 --> 16:55.232
Lou, (STUTTERS) I need
one. I'm asking you for one.

16:55.360 --> 16:57.590
Ed, that's not... No, I've
seen the shows on TV.

16:57.680 --> 16:58.750
No, you don't...

